*/

@node SUBMOVE "Font4D : Coordinates Editor"

  @{" General Purpose of this Editor " Link MPURP} 

  @{" I N F O T E X T ! " Link MEINFO}
  Global:
  @{"        Help        " Link MEHELP} @{"        Undo        " Link MEUNDO} 
  @{"    Load    " Link MELOAD}  @{"    Merge    " Link MEMERG}  @{"    Save    " Link MESAVE} 

  Coordinates: 	       Variables:
  @{"      List of       " Link MELIST} @{" Last Point         " Link MEVARS} 
  |  @{" Coordinates " Link MECOOR}   | @{" Last Control-Point " Link MEVARS} 
  |                  | @{" Next Point         " Link MEVARS} 
  |                  | @{" Next Control-Point " Link MEVARS} 
  |                  | @{" Object Position    " Link MEVARS} 
  |                  | 	
  |                  | 	Functions:
  |                  | @{"         Add        " Link MEADD} 
  |                  | @{"        Remove      " Link MEREMO} 
  |                  | @{"          Up        " Link MEUP} 
  |__________________| @{"         Down       " Link MEDOWN} 

  Edit Coordinates:
   X: @{"    X    " Link MEX}  Y: @{"    Y    " Link MEY}  Z: @{"    Z    " Link MEZ} 

  @{" [ ] Multiply Coordinates ...            " Link MECMVA} 

  @{"         Ok         " Link MEOK} @{"       Cancel       " Link MECANC} 

@Endnode

@node MPURP "Font4D : Movement Editor : General Purpose"

The Movement Editor is used to define movement, by
generating a list of points. These points then define
a curve, an object will follow durining the animation.
Each View-Command specifies such a list of points for 
each object it deals with. If no points are specified
the object will not appear when the View-Command is
executed.
@Endnode

